Laurent Koscielny is Arsene Wenger's latest injury concern after he was released by France to return to Arsenal for treatment on an achilles problem.

The knock is only regarded as minor but it is another headache for Wenger at a time when injuries are piling up at an alarming rate.

Mesut Ozil was sent home from Germany after scans on his left knee revealed ligament damage which is expected to rule him out for up to three months.

