France Football Federation's statement read: 'Since joining [France in] Clairefontaine on Monday, October 6, Laurent Koscielny has been suffering with chronic tendinitis of both achilles tendons for several months.

'Without noting any favourable changes for three days, and after discussion with the player and Franck Le Gall, doctor of the France team, Didier Deschamps decided to release Laurent Koscielny to his club.' 

Arsenal do not expect Koscielny's injury to force him out of action and anticipate he will be fit for their next game, against Hull City, in the Barclays Premier League on Saturday week. 

